<br>
It's been two months now. Why are we still getting zone crashes? Why is there still that heinous memory leak? Why are the servers so goddamned unstable (and they're runnin on LINUX for chrissakes so you can't blame the OS)? Yeah, I know, I know, makin a game is hard and whatnot, and they're trying stuff No One Has Tried Before and blah blah bliddity blah. It's one thing to be ambitious; it's another to not fix shit after two months.<br>
<br>
It's another to blow PR sunshine up my ass every day and tell me everything's milk and honey when I can't yet zone with confidence. I wonder how long it'll be before I don't look at a zone line with fear and loathing.<br>
<br>
So... yeah, they do listen, and yeah, they do seem to respond to issues well, but no, their execution of same is not even nearly up to par, and no, their PR speak doesn't alleviate the pain. <br>
<br>
And remember, it's only been two months. They haven't had the time to become as jaded and bitter as Verant. At the start, Verant wasn't as bad as they are now. We'll see. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uyuzhanvong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yuzhan Vong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#660000>(8/27/01 12:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ebicom.net/~bookster/vonghead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sensei's 08.27.01 Poll.</span><hr size=1> Not to defend Funcom, but they are at least appearing to be putting forth an effort to listen to the customers. Now what they do behind the scenes is anyones guess. <br>
