<img src="http://www.ebicom.net/~bookster/pain.jpg" width="245" height="15"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukezzic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kezzic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#660000>(8/27/01 12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sensei's 08.27.01 Poll.</span><hr size=1> I also voted &quot;No, VI does a better job&quot;.  I suppose it depends on your definition of what &quot;a better game administration company&quot; is.<br>
<br>
Certainly I disagree with many of the policies and decisions made by VI.  In that respect, my own views of what a MMORPG should be seem much closer to those of Funcom:  reduced downtime, making all classes viable, doing away with camping, and so on.  Don't waste my time.  And it seems as if Funcom does care about those issues (and many others).  For those things that aren't working quite right (technical, balance, gameplay and otherwise), I have been led to believe that Funcom will address these and the outcome will be something I agree with.  So far, so good.  I should vote for Funcom, you would think.<br>
<br>
But then there is the reality of the game.  On the technical side, there are complaints from those who even now cannot start the game (though that works for me) or for whom the game is too slow (my 1 GHz CPU, 1 gigabyte of RAM and GF3 video card seem barely adequate).  There are problems with a &quot;memory leak&quot;, lag, zoning.  I have lost items, credits and experience due to bugs.  There are many balance issues (my MA is fine this week, ask me again next week).  There have been and continue to be exploits, and though we are told that exploiters are being handled, the behavior I see in game indicates they are being ignored.  There are griefers running around but they too are ignored despite being reported.  My attempts to contact customer service have been fruitless; I've had more luck in forums such as this one.<br>
<br>
I don't know if Funcom is even aware of the problems in their game.  There are so many of them that only the biggest problems receive official attention in the public forums.  Given the slow pace at which things get fixed, I get the feeling today's little problems will still be there a year from now.  There is no sign that Funcom even attempted to playtest some parts of the game (such as gameplay and balance at level 100+).  Things that get fixed in one patch might be broken with the next patch.  There are serious communications issues (such as the &quot;magic patch&quot; expected the day billing started and the massive exploit that was reported but went live with the 12.5 patch).<br>
<br>
I give Funcom an &quot;A&quot; for PR, &quot;D&quot; for what I actually see.  With VI, at least I knew what I was getting into.  With AO, things might work if I wait long enough.  I disagreed with VI, but at least they had my respect as a &quot;game administration company&quot;.  I think I agree with Funcom (or at least with Funcom's PR), but I no longer respect them.<br>
<br>
For me, it's no longer a question of whether AO is worth paying $10 a month for (I prepaid for 6 months).  The new question is whether AO is worth playing at all (even if it were free).  Part of this is based on how I see Funcom as the game administrator (see above), and another part deals with those things I see as failures in AO's design (which deals more with Funcom as the game developer and would be another long rant).<br>
<br>
FYI, I played EQ for about a year and a half, and quit (twice - came back when Velious was released).  Among my reasons for quitting was a loathing of VI's &quot;vision&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uteffama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TeffaMA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#660000>(8/27/01 1:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sensei's 08.27.01 Poll.</span><hr size=1> Sensei, target someone in the shop and click the clinic , it will raise your skill <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucreode.showPublicProfile?language=EN>creode</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#660000>(8/27/01 1:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sensei's 08.27.01 Poll.</span><hr size=1> **Yes, with some reservations about the future**<br>
